important part is:\n\n```text\nError: Invalid library path .../lib/svm/clibraries/linux-amd64/glibc\nCaused by: java.nio.file.NoSuchFileException: .../lib/svm/clibraries/linux-amd64/glibc\n```\n\nIt occurs during `nativeTestCompile`, after Java compilation and JVM tests have already completed, while Native Image is creating/linking the executable. That means the test sources compiled successfully and Native Image analysis also completed; the failure is an invalid/incomplete GraalVM installation path.\n\nI checked the current environment, and the expected directory now exists:\n\n```text\n$GRAALVM_HOME/lib/svm/clibraries/linux-amd64/glibc\n```\n\nSo this looks like either:\n\n1. the GraalVM symlink/installation was incomplete while the Gradle daemon was running, or\n2. a stale Gradle daemon captured an inconsistent `GRAALVM_HOME` / `JAVA_HOME`.\n\nSuggested recovery:\n\n```bash\n./gradlew --stop\nls -ld \"$(readlink -f \"$GRAALVM_HOME\")/lib/svm/clibraries/linux-amd64/glibc\"\n\"$GRAALVM_HOME/bin/native-image\" --version\n```\n\nThen rerun:\n\n```bash\n./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.google.auto.value:auto-value:1.4.1 --stacktrace\n```\n\nIf it still fails, force a clean native build for this coordinate:\n\n```bash\n./gradlew clean -Pcoordinates=com.google.auto.value:auto-value:1.4.1\n./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.google.auto.value:auto-value:1.4.1 --stacktrace\n```\n\nNo test-code change is indicated by this error.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_085ae166e34addb90169f98b1ce4348196a4108216b96a499b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 928, "output": 831, "cacheRead": 35840, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37599, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777961748329, "responseId": "resp_085ae166e34addb90169f98b14eca88196b465c26b13718138"}}
